<title>Leo Brouwer, Afro-Cuban Composer, Guitarist & Conductor</title>
<meta name="description" content="Leo Brouwer is an Afro-Cuban composer, classical guitarist and conductor who was born in Havana on March 1, 1939.  He has many film scores to his name, including &quot;Like Water for Chocolate&quot;, and has made more than 100 recordings.  Brouwer is founder and director of the Orquesta Cordoba in Spain and of a Guitar Festival in Cuba.">
<meta name="keywords" content="Afro-Cuban Conductor, Afro-Cuban Composer, Afro-Cuban Guitarist, Cinema, Film Scores, Leo Brouwer, Orquesta Cordoba">
